# dist-manifest — the distribution whitelist (ATOM-130, GATE-031, INFO-043).
#
# Principle: a path ships ONLY if it is universal for every instance —
# «универсально целиком или не едет». Everything else (the factory: its
# products/, decisions/, TASKS, launch files, working roles) lives in
# qroky/lab and never reaches a user's machine.
#
# Format: one path per line, relative to the repo root. Directories end
# with «/» and ship whole. Lines starting with # and blank lines are
# ignored. This file drives BOTH the installer's sparse vendoring
# (install.sh) and the freeze check (verify.sh): the two can never
# disagree about what the product is.
framework/
runtime/
distribution/
docs/
knowledge/
qroky.sh
CHANGELOG.md
README.md
LICENSE
MANIFEST.md
CONTRIBUTING.md
.gitignore
